.TH KIRO-DIAG 8 "2026-05-19" "Kiro" "Kiro System Tools"
.SH NAME
kiro-diag \- display Kiro system diagnostic information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kiro-diag
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kiro-diag
prints a concise system snapshot useful for quick diagnosis and bug reports.
.PP
Information displayed:
.IP \(bu 4
ISO version from
.I /etc/dev-rel
.IP \(bu 4
Firmware type: BIOS or UEFI
.IP \(bu 4
Mounted block filesystems and their types
.IP \(bu 4
Active display manager (sddm, gdm, lightdm, lxdm, or ly)
.IP \(bu 4
Available X11 and Wayland session desktop files
.IP \(bu 4
Installed kernel modules under
.I /usr/lib/modules
.IP \(bu 4
Running kernel version from
.I /proc/version
.IP \(bu 4
NVIDIA driver status and installed NVIDIA packages
.IP \(bu 4
GRUB nvidia-drm.modeset flag (if GRUB is present)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a help message and exit (does not require root).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit (does not require root).
.SH NOTES
Must be run as root:
.B sudo kiro-diag
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kiro-report (8),
.BR kiro-audit (8),
.BR kiro-verify (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Erik Dubois <https://www.erikdubois.be>
